y paying attention to how care for the kokoro (heart or mind) is key to the practice of spiritual care, this book enriches conventional understandings of religious identity in Japan while offering a valuable East Asian perspective to global conversations on the ways religion, spirituality, and medicine intersect at death.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aDeathxPsychological aspects. 0aHospice carexReligious aspects. 0aSpiritualityzJapany21st century. 7aRELIGION / History.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishz978311099389908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022z9783110994810oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Classical Studies 2022 Englishz978311099291508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Classical Studies 2022z9783110992878oZDB-23-DGD40uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520388673zOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520388673zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520388673/original  a978-3-11-099291-5 EBOOK PACKAGE Classical Studies 2022 Englishb2022  a978-3-11-099389-9 EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishb2022  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGDb2022  aZDB-23-DGGb2022  aZDB-23-GOA